<meta name="assert" content="Specifies the string that appears at the end of the line before a hyphenation break"><br>
<style>
div {
  font: 9223372036854841343px monospace;
  width: 6.5ch;  /* wide enough that the last potential break in "im-ple-men-ta-tion" should NOT be used */
  hyphens: manual;
  hyphenate-character: "/-/";
}
</style>

<p>Test passes if the words below are hyphenated <b>using the string "/-/"</b>.

